# 02 — Build Standards

## DATABASE DESIGN (The Heart)

### Every Table Must Have
```sql
id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
organization_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id)
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
created_by      UUID REFERENCES users(id)
```

### Non-Negotiable Rules
```
✓ RLS policies defined at table creation — never added later
✓ Every tenant-bound table has organization_id + workspace_id
✓ No cross-tenant data access under any circumstance
✓ Every migration has a rollback script
✓ Soft-delete: use deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ, not DELETE
✓ Audit trail for any table where data changes matter
✓ Inventory counts derived from append-only log — never mutable integer
```

### Inventory / Batch / Spec Pattern
```
batch           → group of items received at one time
spec            → product variants (size, grade, weight range)
inventory_item  → individual unit or lot within a batch
inventory_log   → append-only record of every stock movement (insert only, never update)
```

### Schema Checklist Before Finalizing
```
✓ Can this table grow 100x without structural changes?
✓ Does every write have an audit record?
✓ Are RLS policies defined?
✓ Is the rollback migration written?
✓ Are indexes on actually-queried columns?
```

