## STATE MACHINE DESIGN (The Brain)

Use state machines for any multi-step process. Never use ad-hoc status strings.

### Rules
```
✓ Define ALL valid states before writing any code
✓ Define ALL valid transitions (from → to) explicitly
✓ Every transition: trigger + guard condition + side effects
✓ Invalid transitions must be rejected — not silently ignored
✓ Every state change logged: timestamp, from, to, actor, reason
```

### Design Template (document before coding)
```
States: [all valid states]
Initial state: [starting state]
Terminal states: [cannot transition further]

Transitions:
  [from] → [to]
  Trigger: [what causes this]
  Guard: [conditions that must be true]
  Side effects: [what happens when transition fires]
  On failure: [compensation action if side effects fail]
```

### Rollback Rule
Every transition that triggers external actions must have a compensation action.
Use Trigger.dev for durable multi-step transitions with retry logic.

