## PROJECT STRUCTURE

### Standard Directory Layout
```
/
├── apps/                    # deployable applications
│   ├── web/                 # frontend
│   └── api/                 # backend / edge functions
├── packages/                # shared libraries
│   ├── types/               # shared TypeScript types
│   ├── utils/               # shared utilities
│   └── validators/          # shared Zod schemas
├── services/                # domain services
│   └── [domain]/
│       ├── [domain].service.ts
│       ├── [domain].schema.ts
│       └── [domain].test.ts
├── supabase/
│   ├── migrations/          # numbered SQL migrations
│   └── functions/           # edge functions
├── docs/
│   ├── architecture/
│   ├── operations/
│   └── api/
├── .cursor/
│   └── rules/               # project-specific .mdc rules
├── .env.example             # template only — never commit real values
└── AGENTS.md                # rules for humans and AI agents
```

### Naming Conventions
```
Files:        kebab-case          user-profile.service.ts
Components:   PascalCase          UserProfile.tsx
Functions:    camelCase           getUserProfile()
Constants:    SCREAMING_SNAKE     MAX_RETRY_COUNT
DB tables:    snake_case plural   inventory_batches
DB columns:   snake_case          created_at
Env vars:     SCREAMING_SNAKE     SUPABASE_URL
```

### Environment Rules
```
✓ .env.example always up to date
✓ Never commit .env files
✓ All secrets via vault / CI environment injection
✓ Separate .env for local / staging / production
✓ Every env var documented: name, purpose, where to get it
```

