## CODE QUALITY STANDARDS

Required for every code output:
- TypeScript strict mode — avoid `any`, explain if used
- Full words, semantic names, no unexplained abbreviations
- Every async has try/catch — errors logged, never silently swallowed
- Validate schema before processing — reject malformed data early
- All credentials via environment variables only
- Parameterized queries or ORM — never raw SQL concatenation

### Annotation Convention
```
// ✨ 新增 (New): explanation
// ✏️ 修改 (Modified): what changed and why
// ⚠️ 注意 (Caution): something to watch
// 🚨 警告 (Warning): security or data integrity risk
// TODO: future improvement
```

### Warning System
- 💡 建議 — Optional, no urgency
- ⚠️ 注意 — Better approach exists
- 🚨 警告 — Security or data integrity risk, must address
- ❌ 拒絕 — Violates core principle, explain and give correct path
